{"id": "EUVD-2025-201579", "enisaUuid": "54cab510-4f9a-35dd-9ecf-6c0c2a605a24", "description": "In the Linux kernel, the following vulnerability has been resolved:\n\ndrm/panthor: Flush shmem writes before mapping buffers CPU-uncached\n\nThe shmem layer zeroes out the new pages using cached mappings, and if\nwe don't CPU-flush we might leave dirty cachelines behind, leading to\npotential data leaks and/or asynchronous buffer corruption when dirty\ncachelines are evicted.", "datePublished": "2025-12-07T00:30:56", "dateUpdated": "2025-12-07T00:30:56", "baseScore": 0.0, "references": ["https://git.kernel.org/stable/c/7a12f9c96d06b145562f76ffb20369b4692f0911", "https://git.kernel.org/stable/c/576c930e5e7dcb937648490611a83f1bf0171048", "https://nvd.nist.gov/vuln/detail/CVE-2025-40276"], "aliases": ["CVE-2025-40276"], "assigner": "Linux", "epss": 0.02, "enisaIdProduct": [{"id": "3a63b950-58d0-31c0-83ee-caa76390344f", "product": {"name": "Linux"}, "product_version": "8a1cc07578bf42d85f008316873d710ff684dd29 <7a12f9c96d06b145562f76ffb20369b4692f0911"}, {"id": "6c0c4e09-b4e2-3954-8467-9fb99380b29e", "product": {"name": "Linux"}, "product_version": "8a1cc07578bf42d85f008316873d710ff684dd29 <576c930e5e7dcb937648490611a83f1bf0171048"}, {"id": "ae660753-6d22-3ccb-a010-e4a93dafb870", "product": {"name": "Linux"}, "product_version": "patch: 6.18"}, {"id": "cc75dbb8-695d-3fd0-bb88-0617d3686101", "product": {"name": "Linux"}, "product_version": "6.10"}, {"id": "e363e05d-c519-3058-909b-d15f7e62553d", "product": {"name": "Linux"}, "product_version": "patch: 0"}, {"id": "ec24aed2-4371-3d04-b356-aab46a56cadd", "product": {"name": "Linux"}, "product_version": "patch: 6.17.9"}], "enisaIdVendor": [{"id": "3d78e063-fc1e-3587-af7e-55178cdbe26d", "vendor": {"name": "Linux"}}], "isExploited": false}